Section 1. Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Georgia, and it is hereby enacted by authority of the same, that the Act creating and establishing a new charter for the City of Albany, approved August 18, 1923, as amended, be and the same is hereby amended by striking from said Act as amended that portion of said Act defining the limits of said city, and inserting in lieu thereof a new description of the territory to be included within said city, to wit: Beginning at the intersection of the north line of Seventh Street extended east and the east bank of the Flint River, run west to the west side of what is known as the old Leesburg Road, thence run north along the west side of the old Leesburg Road to the north side of the Seaboard Air-Line right of way, thence run in a north-westerly direction along the north side of the Seaboard Air-Line right of way 3100 feet, thence run due west to the east side of what is commonly known as the Palmyra Road, thence in a southeasterly direction along the east side of said Palmyra Road to the north side of Tenth Street (as shown on map recorded in Book 15, page 355, Dougherty County court-house) extended west, thence run west along the north line of Tenth Street extended west to a corner-stone where the west line of Davis Street extended north intersects, thence run south along said west line of Davis Street extended north to the north line of Ninth Street, thence run west 2864 feet to a corner-stone, thence run south to the south line of Third Street, thence run west to the west side of Baker Avenue, Eugemar Addition (as shown on page 105, Plat Book No. 1, Dougherty County court-house), thence run in a southerly direction along the west side of said Baker Avenue to the northwest side of Lucile Road (Eugemar Addition), thence in a south-westerly direction along the northwest side of said Lucile Road to the northeast side of the Albany-Dawson Public Road, thence run due south to the north side of Board Street extended west, thence run east to the east side of Slappy Drive, thence run south along the east side of Slappy Drive to the south side of South Street extended west, thence run east along the south side of South Street



extended west 1702 feet to a corner stone of the east side of the suburban street known as Harding Street, thence run due south 2132 feet to a corner-stone, thence run east to the west side of a road running north and south along the west line of land lot 335, thence run south along the west side of said road to the south line of land lot 335, thence run due east along the south line of said lot to the east line of land lot 335, thence run south along the west line of land lot (321) three hundred twenty-one 700 feet to a corner-stone, thence run east 1700 feet to a corner-stone, thence run south 700 feet to a corner-stone, thence run east to a corner-stone on the low-water mark on the east bank of Flint River, thence run in a northerly direction along the low-water mark on the east bank of Flint River to a corner-stone on the south side of Boundary Street extended east, thence run east to the east side of new Albany-Camilla paved highway, thence run in a northerly direction along the east side of said road to a corner-stone on the south side of South Street extended east, thence run east to a corner-stone due south from the point where the east side of the right of way of the Georgia Northern Railroad intersects the center line of the Albany-Sylvester Road, thence run north 3490 feet to a corner-stone on the north side of North Street extended east, thence run west to the low-water mark on the east side of Flint River, thence run in a northerly direction along the low-water mark of said Flint River to the point of beginning; provided, that, for the purpose of the exercise by the authority of said city of police power and authority over offenses, matters or things affecting in any manner or degree the public health, peace, good order, safety, or morals, and over persons offending against the laws or city ordinances relative thereto, the corporate limits proper, as above defined, are hereby extended for a distance of one-half mile in every direction from said corporate limits proper, and within said extended corporate limits the power and authority to exercise such police power and authority is hereby vested in and conferred upon the Board of City Commissioners of said city;



and all valid ordinances of said city heretofore or hereafter enacted, relative to or covering said offenses, matters or things, or said offending persons, shall become and be operative and of full force and effect in and through the territory within said extended corporate limits, and said territory shall be known as the city's police limits, and the power and authority is hereby vested in and conferred upon any and all of the police or arresting officers of said city in the enforcement of said ordinances to make arrests, or execute warrants or other process of the city within said territory, and to make arrests therein for the violation of any State law relative to said offenses, matters or things, or offending persons, and all summons, subpoenas, warrants, and writs issued by authority of said city shall be operative and have full force and effect in said territory. Corporate limits.
